		    <title outputclass="H4H3xx" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">552.238-78</ph> Scope of Contract (Eligible Ordering Activities).</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
			      <p otherprops="Body"
            audience="GSAR"
            outputclass="Grey_Body"
            xtrf="Grey"
            class="- topic/p ">As prescribed in <xref href="GSAM-FBCQNJUA.dita#FBCQNJUA"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">538.7004</xref>(b) insert the following clause:</p>
			      <p otherprops="Ctr_SmCaps"
            outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps"
            xtrf="Grey"
            class="- topic/p ">Scope of Contract (Eligible Ordering Activities) (Jul 2016)</p>
			      <ol id="d874e21" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e26"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             This solicitation is issued to establish contracts which may be used on a nonmandatory basis by the agencies and activities named below, as a source of supply for the supplies or services described herein, for domestic and/or overseas delivery. For Special Item Number 132-53, Wireless Services ONLY, limited geographic coverage (consistent with the Offeror's commercial practice) may be proposed.</p>
					          <ol id="d874e31" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e36"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Executive agencies (as defined in FAR subpart 2.1) including nonappropriated fund activities as prescribed in 41 CFR 101-26.000;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e45"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Government contractors authorized in writing by a Federal agency pursuant to FAR 51.1;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e54"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Mixed ownership Government corporations (as defined in the Government Corporation Control Act);</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e63"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Federal Agencies, including establishments in the legislative or judicial branch of government (except the Senate, the House of Representatives and the Architect of the Capitol and any activities under the direction of the Architect of the Capitol).</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e72"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 The District of Columbia;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e82"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Tribal governments when authorized under 25 USC 450j(k);</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e91"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Tribes or tribally designated housing entities pursuant to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">25 U.S.C. 4111(j)</xref>;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e104"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Qualified Nonprofit Agencies as authorized under 40 USC 502(b); and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e113"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(9)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Organizations, other than those identified in paragraph (d) of this clause, authorized by GSA pursuant to statute or regulation to use GSA as a source of supply.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e127"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						              <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Definitions</i>. <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Domestic delivery</i> is delivery within the 48 contiguous states, Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, Washington, DC, and U.S. territories. Domestic delivery also includes a port or consolidation point, within the aforementioned areas, for orders received from overseas activities.</p>
					          <p id="d866e142"
                  outputclass="H5_continued"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">   <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Overseas delivery</i> is delivery to points outside of the 48 contiguous states, Washington, DC, Alaska, Hawaii, Puerto Rico, and U.S. territories.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e154"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             Offerors are requested to check one of the following boxes:</p>
					          <p id="d866e163"
                  outputclass="H5_continued"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">□ Contractor will provide domestic and overseas delivery.</p>
					          <p id="d866e173"
                  outputclass="H5_continued"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">□ Contractor will provide overseas delivery only.</p>
					          <p id="d866e182"
                  outputclass="H5_continued"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">□ Contractor will provide domestic delivery only.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li id="i1874059"
                otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e191"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             The following activities may place orders against Schedule contracts:</p>
					          <ol id="d874e195" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e201"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 State and local government may place orders against Schedule 70 contracts, and Consolidated Schedule contracts containing information technology Special Item Numbers, and Schedule 84 contracts, on an optional basis; PROVIDED, the Contractor accepts order(s) from such activities;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e210"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 The American National Red Cross may place orders against Federal Supply Schedules for products and services in furtherance of the purposes set forth in its Federal charter (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">36 U.S.C. § 300102</xref>); PROVIDED, the Contractor accepts order(s) from the American National Red Cross; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e223"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 Other qualified organizations, as defined in section 309 of the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. § 5152</xref>), may place orders against Federal Supply Schedules for products and services determined to be appropriate to facilitate emergency preparedness and disaster relief and set forth in guidance by the Administrator of General Services, in consultation with the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency; PROVIDED, the Contractor accepts order(s) from such activities.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e236"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 State and local governments may place orders against Federal Supply Schedules for good or services determined by the Secretary of Homeland Security to facilitate recovery from a major disaster declared by the President under the Robert T. Stafford Disaster Relief and Emergency Assistance Act (<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42 U.S.C. 5121</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">et seq</i>.) to facilitate disaster preparedness or response, or to facilitate recovery from terrorism or nuclear, biological, chemical, or radiological attack; PROVIDED, the Contractor accepts order(s) from such activities.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e254"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             Articles or services may be ordered from time to time in such quantities as may be needed to fill any requirement, subject to the Order Limitations thresholds which will be specified in resultant contracts. Overseas activities may place orders directly with schedule contractors for delivery to CONUS port or consolidation point.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li props="Runin"
                otherprops="H5_6_abc123"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="id1937G500U5Z"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            
					          </p>
					          <ol id="d874e267" xtrf="Grey" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="id1937GD00DY4"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 The Contractor is obligated to accept orders received from activities within the Executive branch of the Federal Government.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li otherprops="123"
                      audience="GSAR"
                      outputclass="Grey_H6_123"
                      xtrf="Grey"
                      class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d866e273"
                        outputclass="H6_123"
                        xtrf="Grey"
                        class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                 The Contractor is not obligated to accept orders received from activities outside the Executive branch; however, the Contractor is encouraged to accept such orders. If the Contractor elects to accept such orders, all provisions of the contract shall apply, including clause 552.232-79, Payment by Credit Card. If the Contractor is unwilling to accept such orders, and the proposed method of payment is not through the Credit Card, the Contractor shall return the order by mail or other means of delivery within 5 workdays from receipt. If the Contractor is unwilling to accept such orders, and the proposed method of payment is through the Credit Card, the Contractor must so advise the ordering activity within 24 hours of receipt of order. (Reference clause 552.232-79, Payment by Credit Card.) Failure to return an order or advise the ordering activity within the time frames of this paragraph shall constitute acceptance whereupon all provisions of the contract shall apply.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e284"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(g)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             The Government is obligated to purchase under each resultant contract a guaranteed minimum of $2,500 (two thousand, five hundred dollars) during the contract term.</p>
				        </li>
				        <li otherprops="abc"
                audience="GSAR"
                outputclass="Grey_H5_abc"
                xtrf="Grey"
                class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d866e294"
                  outputclass="H5_abc"
                  xtrf="Grey"
                  class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(h)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						             All users of GSA’s Federal Supply Schedules, including non-Federal users, shall use the schedules in accordance with the ordering guidance provided by the Administrator of General Services. GSA encourages non-Federal users to follow the Schedule Ordering Procedures set forth in the Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) 8.4, but they may use different established competitive ordering procedures if such procedures are needed to satisfy their state and local acquisition regulations and/or organizational policies.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
			      <p otherprops="Body_Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
